Articles.Content: This thing is driving me nuts. So I download 1_5_6 and put it in gamedata. And ever since I get a pop-up when I start the game saying that im using an old version. And I cant for the life of me figure it out. Ive gone though everyone of my mods to see if there are any loose .cgf's anywhere and nothing. I had tried ECLSS earlier and it seemed that was not functioning. This and many other mods use MM so this has to work. Any advise?

This thread made me smile.

Not longer than five minutes ago, I started looking around the forums for the same exact answer!

I don't even know what happens if I don't update it. Everything seems to be running just fine.

There is another module manager dll somewhere in your GameData directory, and that needs to go. It's probably hiding in a mod folder somewhere. Make sure there's only one copy of Module Manager anywhere, or bad things can happen.

Gee, thanks windows search..

I looked for what seemed like an hour. I see your post.. I look one last time. Kerbpaint... it was in Kerb****ing paint. I forgot I even installed that mod. Somehow I overlooked it.

Works now. Go figure. Ty ferram.
The popup display the exact path of the file you need to delete ...
